Package jsocket.exceptions

  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    CryptoKeyAlreadySetException
    Used if encryption key is already set for a cryptographic service
    DatagramConnectionException
    Exception is used by Datagram
    DecryptionFailureException
    Thrown if default cryptographic services fail to decrypt data
    EncryptionFailureException
    Thrown if default cryptographic services fail to encrypt data
    FailedToInitializeException
    Thrown if ciphers used by cryptographic services fail to initialize
    InstantiationException
    Thrown if an exception occurs during constructor call
    InvalidAESKeyLengthException
    Thrown if specified key length is invalid for AES encryption
    MalformedJsonException
    Thrown if string is not in proper JSON format
    SetSocketTimeoutFailureException
    Exception is used by Socket.setSoTimeout(int)
    SocketStreamException
    Thrown if an exception occurs while performing an I/O operation on a stream
    SocketTimeoutException
    Exception is used by Socket
    UninitializedCipherException
    Thrown if ciphers have not been initialized prior to using the cryptographic service
    UnsupportedAlgorithmException
    Thrown if cryptographic service does not support an algorithm
